   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>D. The Sins of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>and the Punishments of Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>concerning Israel s Stubbornness</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Hosea 4:15-19 is concerned with Israel s stubbornness.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Israel Going About as a Harlot</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Israel went about as a harlot, but Judah was charged not to transgress and not to come to Gilgal, nor to go up to Beth-aven, nor to swear, As Jehovah lives v. 15 . Gilgal was the focus of idolatry 9:15; 12:11; Amos 4:4; 5:5 . Beth-aven means house of nothingness or house of idolatry.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Israel Being Stubborn, like a Stubborn Heifer</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Israel was stubborn, like a stubborn heifer Hosea 4:16a , which is disobedient and goes its own way.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Jehovah Limiting Israel in a Narrow Field</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>In verse 16b the prophet asks, Will Jehovah now pasture them / Like a lamb in a spacious place?</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>This indicates that Jehovah would limit Israel in a narrow field.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Ephraim Being Joined to Idols</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>In verse 17a we are told that Ephraim was joined to idols.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Ephraim Being Left Alone</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In 4:17b the prophet gives a charge concerning Ephraim: Leave him alone.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Ephraim was to be let go.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>This indicates a kind of punishment.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>6.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Their Liquor Having Ended,</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>and They Having Given Themselves Up to Harlotry</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Their liquor had ended v. 18a , meaning that their pleasure in drinking was gone.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>That was God s punishment.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>They had given themselves up to harlotry; their rulers dearly loved shame v. 18b . They were fond of drinking and harlotry.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>7.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The Wind Having Wrapped Her Up in Its Wings</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Verse 19a says that the wind had wrapped her up in its wings.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>It had carried her away a kind of punishment.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>According to verse 19b, they would be ashamed because of their sacrifices to idols v. 13a .</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>E. The Sins of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>and the Punishments of Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Mainly concerning the Priests,</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>the House of the King, and the Princes</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>In 5:1-14 and 6:4-10 we have more details about the sins of Israel and the punishments of Jehovah mainly concerning the priests, the house of the king, and the princes.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Jehovah s Judgment Coming</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>upon the Priests, upon the House of Israel,</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>and upon the House of the King</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>In 5:1-2 we are told that upon the priests, upon the house of Israel, and upon the house of the king Jehovah s judgment would come, for they had been a snare and a net for slaughtering, even though Jehovah had chastised them all.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Ephraim Having Gone About as a Harlot,</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>and Israel Being Defiled</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Ephraim had gone about as a harlot, and Israel was defiled.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>A spirit of harlotries was within them or, in the midst of them .</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>Their doings did not permit them to turn to their God, and they did not know Jehovah vv.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>3-4 .</S>
   </TEXT>
